{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"shellUnquote","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"quotedString","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Function","symbolKind":"func","title":"shellUnquote(quotedString:)","externalID":"s:4GLib12shellUnquote12quotedStringSSSgSPys4Int8VGSg_tKF"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unquotes a string as the shell (\/bin\/sh) would."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"shellUnquote","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"quotedString","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function only handles quotes; if a string contains file globs,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"arithmetic operators, variables, backticks, redirections, or other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"special-to-the-shell features, the result will be different from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"result a real shell would produce (the variables, backticks, etc."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will be passed through literally instead of being expanded)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is guaranteed to succeed if applied to the result of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_shell_quote()"},{"type":"text","text":". If it fails, it returns "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"error.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"quotedString","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" need not actually contain quoted or escaped text;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_shell_unquote()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" simply goes through the string and unquotes\/unescapes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"anything that the shell would. Both single and double quotes are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handled, as are escapes including escaped newlines."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The return value must be freed with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_free()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible errors are in the "},{"code":"G_SHELL_ERROR","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" domain."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Shell quoting rules are a bit strange. Single quotes preserve the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"literal string exactly. escape sequences are not allowed; not even"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\\'","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" - if you want a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"'"},{"text":" in the quoted text, you have to do something","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"'foo'\\''bar'"},{"text":". Double quotes allow ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$"},{"type":"text","text":", ```, "},{"code":"\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", ``, and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"newline to be escaped with backslash. Otherwise double quotes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"preserve things literally.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/shellUnquote(quotedString:)"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/shellunquote(quotedstring:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/shellUnquote(quotedString:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/shellUnquote(quotedString:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"shellUnquote","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"quotedString","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">!) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unquotes a string as the shell (\/bin\/sh) would."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/shellunquote(quotedstring:)","role":"symbol","title":"shellUnquote(quotedString:)","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type